Ward
====

Ward is a native macOS configuration organizer for AI coding harnesses
(Claude Code and Codex CLI).

Ward is a from-scratch reimplementation. Its feature set and product design
were inspired by the open-source project:

    Cross-Code Organizer (CCO)
    @mcpware/cross-code-organizer
    Copyright (c) 2026 mcpware
    Licensed under the MIT License
    https://github.com/mcpware/cross-code-organizer

Ward reuses no verbatim source code from CCO; the backend is an independent
Rust implementation and the frontend is an independent redesign. This notice
is provided as a good-faith acknowledgment of CCO as the original inspiration.

Ward's usage engine (src-tauri/src/usage/) ports the 5-hour session-block
algorithm and pricing approach from ccusage (https://github.com/ryoppippi/ccusage,
MIT © 2025 ryoppippi) and its Rust ports ccstat (MIT) and ccusage-in-rust
(BSD-3-Clause). No source was copied verbatim; the algorithm was reimplemented
for Ward's data model.

Ward's live usage path (src-tauri/src/usage/live.rs) reads the subscription
5-hour and weekly limit utilization from the Anthropic API's
`anthropic-ratelimit-unified-*` response headers. This technique is used by
several open-source Claude usage monitors, including claude-monitor
(https://github.com/rjwalters/claude-monitor) and CCSeva
(https://github.com/Iamshankhadeep/ccseva), both MIT. No source was copied;
Ward's implementation is independent. The call is gated behind an explicit
opt-in and reads the user's own OAuth token from the macOS Keychain solely to
authenticate the request to Anthropic; the token is never stored or transmitted
elsewhere.
